-- Hinduja Leyland Finance Plans to Raise 1 Billion Rupees
-- B y   G a n e s h   N a g a r a j a n
-- 2012-02-23T03:12:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/hinduja-leyland-finance-plans-to-raise-1-billion-rupees.html
Hinduja Leyland Finance, a unit of
 Ashok Leyland Ltd. (AL) , plans to raise 1 billion rupees in private
equity investment to increase lending to buyers of light
commercial vehicles and three-wheelers.  The company is looking to rope in a private equity investor
to raise disbursals for the year starting April 1, Managing
Director S. Nagarajan said in an interview yesterday evening.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ganesh Nagarajan in Chennai at 
 gnagarajan1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
